            "title": "Write a Java Program to reverse a string without using String inbuilt",
            "problem": "Write a Java Program to reverse a string without using String inbuilt \nfunction.",
            "solution": "public String reverseString(String input) { \n    char[] chars = input.toCharArray(); \n    int left = 0, right = chars.length - 1; \n    while (left < right) { \n        char temp = chars[left]; \n        chars[left] = chars[right]; \n        chars[right] = temp; \n        left++; \n        right--; \n    } \n    return new String(chars); \n}",
            "explanation": "This solution manually swaps the characters of the string from the start and \nend, moving towards the center, effectively reversing the string without using any built-in \nfunctions."
