            "id": "Q #16)",
            "title": "Given an array nums and a value val, remove all instances of that",
            "problem": "Given an array nums and a value val, remove all instances of that \nvalue in-place and return the new length of the array. Do not allocate extra \nspace for another array. You must modify the input array in-place with O(1) \nextra memory.",
            "solution": "public int removeElement(int[] nums, int val) { \n    int i = 0; \n    for (int j = 0; j < nums.length; j++) { \n            nums[i] = nums[j]; \n            i++; \n        } \n    } \n    return i; \n}",
