            "title": "You are given an n x n 2D matrix representing an image, rotate the",
            "problem": "You are given an n x n 2D matrix representing an image, rotate the \nimage by 90 degrees (clockwise).",
            "solution": "public void rotate(int[][] matrix) { \n    int n = matrix.length; \n    // Transpose the matrix \n    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) { \n        for (int j = i; j < n; j++) { \n            int temp = matrix[j][i]; \n            matrix[j][i] = matrix[i][j]; \n            matrix[i][j] = temp; \n        } \n    } \n    // Reverse each row \n    for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) { \n        for (int j = 0; j < n / 2; j++) { \n            int temp = matrix[i][j]; \n            matrix[i][j] = matrix[i][n - 1 - j]; \n            matrix[i][n - 1 - j] = temp; \n        } \n    } \n}",
            "explanation": "The matrix is rotated by first transposing it (swapping rows with columns) and \nthen reversing each row."
